author: lundblad
msg: Plug memory leak in UTF-8 routines.
(He traced the leak to the new xlate handle caching.)
(get_xlate_handle_node): Get handle from global hash via pointer to
pointer. This means we don't call apr_hash_set() for each translation.
(put_xlate_handle_node): STore handle via pointer to pointer. Manipulate that
pointer instead of updating the hash table.
